    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT27-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">piriviṭai āṟṟāḷ eṉak kavaṉṟa tōḻikkuk kiḻatti uraittatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Declared by HER to the confidante who was anxious she would not have the strength in the time of separation.</p>
          </div>



        <div xml:id="KT27">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                kaṉṟu muṇṇātu kalattiṉum paṭātu</l>
<l>                nallāṉ ṟīmpā ṉilattuk kāaṅ</l>
<l>                keṉakku mākā teṉṉaikku mutavātu</l>
<l>                pacalai yuṇīiya vēṇṭun</l>
<l>                titalai yalkuleṉ māmaik kaviṉē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
               <l rend="indent">Like milk of a good cow spilled on the floor,</l> 
               <l rend="indent2">not eaten by the calf and not in the pot,</l>
               <l rend="indent">of no use to me and not given to my lord</l>
               <l rend="indent3">must pallor eat<note place="foot">The construction of <term xml:lang="ta">uṇīiyar vēṇṭum</term> can either be: "it is necessary for the pallor to eat the beauty" or "it is necessary for the beauty to eat pallor (= to absorb)".</note></l>
               <l rend="indent4">my dark beauty, beauty spots on the hip.</l>
                
                </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
